invalidate.label: invalidate
invalidate.description: Removes an instance from the cache system.

iscached.label: iscached
iscached.description: Checks whether an instance is cached.

replace.label: replace
replace.description: Replaces a cached instance with another.

base64encode.label: base64encode
base64encode.description: encodes a string with Base64 encoding.

base64decode.label: base64decode
base64decode.description: decodes a Base64-encoded string back into its original form.

lz4compress.label: lz4compress
lz4compress.description: compresses a string with the LZ4 compression algorithm.

lz4decompress.label: lz4decompress
lz4decompress.description: decompresses a string that was encoded using the LZ4 compression algorithm back to regular data.

encrypt.label: encrypt
encrypt.description: Encrypts data using a cryptographic algorithm.

hash.label: hash
hash.description: Creates a cryptographic hash of input data.

getconstant.label: getconstant
getconstant.description: returns the constant at the specified index from a Luau function. If no constant exists at that index, it returns nil instead.This is useful when you want to inspect specific constant values (such as strings, numbers, or booleans) without dumping the entire list.

getconstants.label: getconstants
getconstants.description: returns a list of all constants used within a Luau function's bytecode. This includes literal values like numbers, strings, booleans, and nil.

getinfo.label: getinfo
getinfo.description: Returns debug information about a function.

getproto.label: getproto
getproto.description: returns a specific function prototype from a Luau function by index. Optionally, it can search for active functions of the proto, if the activated parameter is set to true.These are internal function definitions (e.g. nested functions) that exist as part of the compiled bytecode, even if they aren't assigned or called.

getprotos.label: getprotos
getprotos.description: returns all function prototypes defined within the specified Luau function.These are internal function definitions (e.g. nested functions) that exist as part of the compiled bytecode, even if they aren't assigned or called.

getstack.label: getstack
getstack.description: retrieves values from the stack at the specified call level.This function is useful for inspecting local variables or arguments at different layers of the stack frame. If no index is given, all values at that stack level are returned as a list.

getupvalue.label: getupvalue
getupvalue.description: returns a list of upvalues captured by a Luau function. These are the external variables that a function closes over from its surrounding scope.If the function has no upvalues, the result will be an empty table.

getupvalues.label: getupvalues
getupvalues.description: Returns all upvalues from a function.

setconstant.label: setconstant
setconstant.description: modifies a constant at the specified index in a Luau function bytecode.This can be used to change hardcoded behavior within functions without modifying their source code - although it requires knowing the correct constant index beforehand.

setstack.label: setstack
setstack.description: replaces a value in a specified stack frame.This allows for powerful manipulation of runtime variables or arguments, particularly useful in advanced debugging or dynamic patching scenarios.

setupvalue.label: setupvalue
setupvalue.description: replaces an upvalue at the specified index in a Luau function, with a new value.This allows for controlled modification of function state, often used in hooking or testing environments.

readfile.label: readfile
readfile.description: retrieves the contents of a file at the specified path and returns it as a string.If the file does not exist or cannot be accessed, the function will error.

listfiles.label: listfiles
listfiles.description: returns an array of strings representing all files and folders within the specified directory.This can be used to dynamically check which files exist in a folder, etc.

writefile.label: writefile
writefile.description: writes data to a file at the specified path. If the file already exists, its contents will be overwritten.This is one of the primary ways to persist string data within the executor's file sandbox.

makefolder.label: makefolder
makefolder.description: creates a folder at the specified path if one does not already exist.This is useful for organising files into separate directories.

appendfile.label: appendfile
appendfile.description: appends string content to the end of a file at the specified path. If the file does not exist, it will be created.This is useful for logging, accumulating data over time, or extending file contents without overwriting them.

isfile.label: isfile
isfile.description: checks whether a given path exists and refers to a file.This function is useful when validating input, confirming file existence before reading, or filtering entries returned by listfiles.

isfolder.label: isfolder
isfolder.description: checks whether a given path exists and refers to a folder.This is useful when verifying that a directory exists before writing files into it or listing its contents.

delfolder.label: delfolder
delfolder.description: deletes the folder at the specified path if it exists.

delfile.label: delfile
delfile.description: deletes the file at the specified path if it exists.This is useful for cleaning up temporary data or removing no-longer-needed files at runtime.

loadfile.label: loadfile
loadfile.description: compiles the Luau source code from a file and returns the resulting function (chunk). This chunk runs in the global environment.If the file contains syntax errors, an error is thrown - just like loadstring. The error will appear in the console.

dofile.label: dofile
dofile.description: Loads and executes a Lua file.

clonefunction.label: clonefunction
clonefunction.description: creates and returns a new function that has the exact same behaviour as the passed function.

hookfunction.label: hookfunction
hookfunction.description: allows you to hook a function with another wanted function, returning the original unhooked function.

iscclosure.label: iscclosure
iscclosure.description: checks whether a given function is a C closure or not.

islclosure.label: islclosure
islclosure.description: checks whether a given function is a Luau closure or not.

isexecutorclosure.label: isexecutorclosure
isexecutorclosure.description: checks whether a given function is a closure of the executor. This also includes closures retrieved using getscriptclosure or loadstring

newcclosure.label: newcclosure
newcclosure.description: takes any Luau function and wraps it into a C closure. When the returned function is called, it invokes the original Luau closure with the provided arguments, then passes the closure's returned values back to the caller.

cloneref.label: cloneref
cloneref.description: returns a reference clone of an Instance. The returned object behaves identically to the original but is not strictly equal (==) to it.This is commonly used to safely interact with services such as game.CoreGui, making weak-table style attacks fail.

compareinstances.label: compareinstances
compareinstances.description: checks if two Instances are equal.This is primarily used for instances which have been cloneref'd, where the normal equality check with == fails.

fireclickdetector.label: fireclickdetector
fireclickdetector.description: triggers a ClickDetector event. By default, it fires the MouseClick event.

rconsoleinput.label: rconsoleinput
rconsoleinput.description: Reads input from the executor console.

getgc.label: getgc
getgc.description: returns a list of non-dead garbage-collectable values. These include functions, userdatas, and optionally tables.

getgenv.label: getgenv
getgenv.description: returns the executor's global environment table, which is shared across all executor-made threads.

getloadedmodules.label: getloadedmodules
getloadedmodules.description: returns a list of all ModuleScript instances that have been loaded (e.g. require'd).This includes only modules with completed executions, and excludes any modules that errored or haven't been required yet.

getrenv.label: getrenv
getrenv.description: returns the Roblox global environment, which is used by the entire game. Changes to this environment will affect your executor environment as well.

gethui.label: gethui
gethui.description: returns a hidden Instance container used for safely storing UI elements. This container is mainly designed to avoid detections.

checkcaller.label: checkcaller
checkcaller.description: returns a boolean indicating whether the current function was invoked from the executor's own thread. This is useful for differentiating between your own calls and those made by the game.

isrbxactive.label: isrbxactive
isrbxactive.description: Checks if Roblox window is active.

getthreadidentity.label: getthreadidentity
getthreadidentity.description: retrieves the thread's identity of the running Luau thread.

setthreadidentity.label: setthreadidentity
setthreadidentity.description: sets the current Luau thread identity and capabilities matching that identity.This is commonly used alongside functions like gethiddenproperty or getconnections which may require elevated access.

getrunningscripts.label: getrunningscripts
getrunningscripts.description: returns a list of all running scripts in the caller's global state. This includes Script, LocalScript, and ModuleScript instances - excluding CoreScripts by default.

getscriptbytecode.label: getscriptbytecode
getscriptbytecode.description: retrieves the bytecode of a LocalScript, ModuleScript, and Script.

getscripthash.label: getscripthash
getscripthash.description: getscripthash returns a SHA-384 hash in hexadecimal format of the raw bytecode for a given Script, LocalScript, or ModuleScript.This is useful for identifying scripts by their content, especially when checking for known modules or verifying integrity.

getscripts.label: getscripts
getscripts.description: returns a list of all Script, LocalScript, and ModuleScript instances present.This function excludes CoreScripts by default.

getsenv.label: getsenv
getsenv.description: returns the global environment table of a given Script, LocalScript, or ModuleScript.This environment contains all global variables and functions available to the target script, such as custom-defined functions or state values.

getcallingscript.label: getcallingscript
getcallingscript.description: returns the Script, LocalScript, or ModuleScript that triggered the current code execution.

getscriptclosure.label: getscriptclosure
getscriptclosure.description: getscriptclosure creates and returns a Luau function closure from the compiled bytecode of a Script, LocalScript, or ModuleScript.This function is often used to extract constants or behaviour from scripts without needing to run them inside the game.

isrenderobj.label: isrenderobj
isrenderobj.description: checks whether a given value is a valid Drawing object.This is useful for validation in functions or modules that work with custom render systems.

getrenderproperty.label: getrenderproperty
getrenderproperty.description: retrieves the value of a property from a Drawing object. This behaves identically to using object[property], but is useful when working with dynamic property names or for reflection-like access.

setrenderproperty.label: setrenderproperty
setrenderproperty.description: assigns a value to a property of a Drawing object. This behaves identically to object[property] = value, but is useful for dynamic or abstracted property access.

cleardrawcache.label: cleardrawcache
cleardrawcache.description: removes all active drawing objects created with Drawing.new.

WebSocket.label: WebSocket
WebSocket.description: The WebSocket class provides a lightweight interface for establishing and working with WebSocket connections. It allows scripts to send and receive messages over a persistent connection to a WebSocket server.

request.label: request
request.description: sends a HTTP request to the given URL using the provided configuration table. It yields until the request is complete and returns a structured response.

mouse1press.label: mouse1press
mouse1press.description: Simulates pressing the left mouse button.

mouse1release.label: mouse1release
mouse1release.description: Simulates releasing the left mouse button.

mouse2press.label: mouse2press
mouse2press.description: Simulates pressing the right mouse button.

mouse2release.label: mouse2release
mouse2release.description: Simulates releasing the right mouse button.

mousemoveabs.label: mousemoveabs
mousemoveabs.description: Moves the mouse to absolute coordinates.

mousemoverel.label: mousemoverel
mousemoverel.description: Moves the mouse relative to its current position.

getrawmetatable.label: getrawmetatable
getrawmetatable.description: returns the raw metatable of an object, even if that object has a __metatable field set.

hookmetamethod.label: hookmetamethod
hookmetamethod.description: takes any Luau object that can have a metatable, and attempts to hook the specified metamethod of the object. Internally, it essentially uses hookfunction to hook specific metamethods.

getnamecallmethod.label: getnamecallmethod
getnamecallmethod.description: returns the name of the method that invoked the __namecall metamethod.When used inside a hookmetamethod hook targeting __namecall, it will attempt to retrieve the method being called (e.g. InvokeServer).When used outside of said hook, this function will safely return nil.

isreadonly.label: isreadonly
isreadonly.description: checks whether a table is currently set as readonly.

setrawmetatable.label: setrawmetatable
setrawmetatable.description: forcibly sets the metatable of a value, bypassing the __metatable protection field.

setreadonly.label: setreadonly
setreadonly.description: sets whether a table is readonly or writable.

identifyexecutor.label: identifyexecutor
identifyexecutor.description: returns the name and version of the currently running executor.

queue_on_teleport.label: queue_on_teleport
queue_on_teleport.description: Queues code to run when joining a new game.

getcallbackvalue.label: getcallbackvalue
getcallbackvalue.description: retrieves the assigned callback property on an Instance, such as OnInvoke.Normally, these properties are write-only, meaning you can assign a function to them but cannot read them back. This function bypasses that limitation and exposes the function directly.

getconnections.label: getconnections
getconnections.description: retrieves a list of Connection objects currently attached to a given RBXScriptSignal.

getcustomasset.label: getcustomasset
getcustomasset.description: returns a content ID (e.g. rbxasset://) that can be used in Roblox APIs for loading audio, meshes, UI images, and other asset types.Internally, the file at the given path is copied to the game's content directory and then exposed with a usable asset URL.

gethiddenproperty.label: gethiddenproperty
gethiddenproperty.description: gethiddenproperty retrieves the value of a hidden or non-scriptable property (e.g. BinaryString, SharedString, SystemAddress) from a given Instance, even if it would normally throw an error when accessed directly.This function also returns whether the accessed property was hidden.

sethiddenproperty.label: sethiddenproperty
sethiddenproperty.description: sethiddenproperty assigns a value to a hidden or non-scriptable property of an Instance, even if that property is normally read-only or inaccessible.It returns true if the property is hidden and was successfully written to, or false if the property wasn't hidden but was still updated.

getinstances.label: getinstances
getinstances.description: retrieves every Instance from the registry. Which means that instances that are/were parented to nil will also be returned.

getnilinstances.label: getnilinstances
getnilinstances.description: returns a list of Instance objects that are currently unparented. These instances exist in memory but are no longer part of the DataModel hierarchy.

isscriptable.label: isscriptable
isscriptable.description: returns whether the given property of an Instance is scriptable (i.e. it does not have the notscriptable tag).If it returns true, then the property is scriptable and can be indexed normally, and vice versa.If it returns nil, then the property provided does not exist.

setscriptable.label: setscriptable
setscriptable.description: toggles the scriptability of a hidden or non-scriptable property on an Instance. When a property is made scriptable, it can be accessed or assigned through standard indexing.
